params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.annotation_spec
params.description: The annotation spec of the label for which the precision-recall curve calculated. If this field is empty, that means the precision-recall curve is an aggregate curve for all labels.

params.name: data.area_under_curve
params.description: Area under the precision-recall curve. Not to be confused with area under a receiver operating characteristic (ROC) curve.

params.name: data.confidence_metrics_entries
params.description: Entries that make up the precision-recall graph. Each entry is a "point" on the graph drawn for a different confidence_threshold.
